article.headline: S.C.-Upstate 71, Kennesaw State 65
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. (AP) -- Bobby Davis scored 24 points and pulled down 11 rebounds to lead South Carolina Upstate to a 71-65 win over Kennesaw State on Friday night. The Spartans (5-17, 3-5 Atlantic Sun Conference) scored eight straight points in the final three minutes to take a 66-60 lead with 36 seconds to go. The Owls (6-16, 3-5) cut their deficit to two points on Jonathan Whipple's jumper with six seconds left, but Josh Chavis hit all four of his free throws in less than three seconds to seal the win for SC Upstate. It was a back-and-forth game that saw Kennesaw State build an eight-point lead in the first half. The Spartans came back and had a 57-47 lead with 5:36 to go before the Owls scored 10 straight points in just over two minutes to tie the game. The Spartans dominated the inside, pulling down 43 rebounds -- 17 more than Kennesaw State -- and outscoring the Owls 36-16 in the paint. Ronell Wooten led Kennesaw State with 20 points, while Shuan Stegall added 14 points and seven rebounds. Luke Payne scored 13 points and Nick Schneiders added six points and 10 rebounds for SC Upstate.
